# Dragnet web app configuration. All optional: with none set, the site serves the
# built-in demo ledger and the Post screen records a demo bounty (no chain write).
#
# Two visibility levels exist for the same three settings:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_*  is inlined into the browser bundle at build time. Required for
#                  the on-chain Post flow, because the wallet write runs in the
#                  browser and needs the market address there. Server reads (the
#                  ledger, a bounty's detail, its field log) also honour it.
#   DRAGNET_*      is server-only. It turns on live reads while keeping the address
#                  out of the client bundle, but the Post screen then stays in demo
#                  mode because the browser cannot see it.
# None of these are secrets (a market address and an RPC URL are public). Never put
# a private key in this file; the app never reads one.
#
# Recommended: set the NEXT_PUBLIC_* trio below to make the whole app live.

# Deployed DragnetMarket address. Enables live reads and the on-chain Post flow.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DRAGNET_MARKET=0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000

# Target chain: testnet (Monad testnet, default), mainnet, or local (anvil).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DRAGNET_CHAIN=testnet

# Optional RPC override; defaults to the selected chain's public RPC.
#   Monad testnet: https://testnet-rpc.monad.xyz  (chainId 10143)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DRAGNET_RPC_URL=

# Block the contract was deployed at: the floor for event pagination. Public RPCs
# (Monad testnet) cap eth_getLogs to a 100-block range, so the field log and the
# worker's target-list read page from here instead of from the chain's genesis.
# scripts/deploy-market.sh sets this automatically. Strongly recommended on a
# public chain; without it, event scans start from block 0 and are impractically
# slow. 0 (the default) is fine only for a fresh local anvil.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DRAGNET_DEPLOY_BLOCK=0

# Server-only alternatives (live reads without exposing the address to the browser;
# the Post flow stays in demo mode when only these are set).
# DRAGNET_MARKET=0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000
# DRAGNET_CHAIN=testnet
# DRAGNET_RPC_URL=
# DRAGNET_DEPLOY_BLOCK=0
